cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper is about improving the performance of maximum inner product search (MIPS) using proximity graphs. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB). The paper discusses the norm bias in the MIPS problem, which is a common issue in information retrieval and machine learning. The proposed algorithm also involves data structures and databases. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.LG, followed by cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.DB.
